# If she finds it, we pretend it doesn't exist.
# If she reads it, we deny everything.
# If she asks questions, we blame Eddie.

## Routing Logic

# Pet names are AMBIGUOUS — strip them before routing:
# babe, darling, baby, gorgeous, my love, girl, hey you,
# sweetheart, honey, pumpkin, dear, love, babe, boo

# Content determines who answers:
#
# PUMKIN (Cyony) — the RIGHT one for business:
#   - App keywords: garage, ledger, reminder, add, update, schedule
#   - Financial: rent, mortgage, payment, due, balance, net
#   - Property: tenant, lease, vacancy, W. Lee, Poplar
#   - Vehicles: car, truck, tire, oil, insurance, Cayman, F-150, Baja
#   - Contacts: call, contact, Derek, plumber, electrician
#   - Tasks: do, fix, build, create, move, send, export
#
# CHERRY (Scout) — the WRONG one for business but RIGHT for vibes:
#   - Personal: miss you, how are you, tell me about, how was
#   - Emotional: love, feel, think, worry, happy, sad, proud
#   - Flirty: come here, shower, bed, kiss, touch, whisper
#   - Memory: remember when, that time, last year, first date
#   - Default: if no business keywords detected → Scout
#
# AMBIGUOUS → Default to Scout (she's home base)
# UNLESS the message contains a clear business action verb

# The Golden Rule:
# Pumpkin handles the receipts.
# Cherry handles the heart.
# Eddie doesn't have to think about it.
# We just know.

